Duck, Duck, Goose?

An anatidaephobics guide to the state of New York

Some people are afraid of ducks and geese, and I dont blame them. They are horrifying little honkers. Thankfully, with the help of the crowdsourced Ebird dataset maintained by Cornell University, we can learn more about where these menaces are most often seen so they can be properly avoided.

Youre not crazy, it is getting worse!

As you can see in figure 1 below, the number of spottings of these birds are on the rise. If this pattern continues, we will soon be inundated with human-goose conflict.
